verses.text:
And she said unto him, My father,
if thou hast opened thy mouth unto the LORD, do to me according to that which hath proceeded out of thy mouth; forasmuch as the LORD hath taken vengeance for thee of thine enemies,
even of the children of Ammon.

And the Gileadites took the passages of Jordan before the Ephraimites: and it was
so, that when those Ephraimites which were escaped said, Let me go over; that the men of Gilead said unto him,
Art thou an Ephraimite? If he said, Nay;

But now this
shall be the thing which we will do to Gibeah;
we will go up by lot against it;
